 Key Sections and Location of Disclosures\n- The primary definitions, methodology, and limitations for **Family metrics (DAP and ARPP)** are detailed in the preamble sections under "Limitations of Key Metrics and Other Data."\n- Risks related to user retention, engagement, and the accuracy of these metrics are discussed in the **Risk Factors** section.\n- The **Management\'s Discussion and Analysis (MD&A)** section (Item 7) references these metrics and directs readers to the limitations section.\n\n**Conclusion**: According to the provided excerpts from Meta\'s 10-K, the company reports and defines **Daily Active People (DAP)** but **does not disclose or define a Monthly Active User (MAU) or Monthly Active People (MAP) metric**. The search for a monthly metric within your provided text yielded no results.\n\nIf you need me to search for a monthly metric in a *different* document or a more complete version of the 10-K, please provide the specific text or source.',
